Hi Lindsay,

As we talked about, here's the table showing the three potential conclusion=
s for any investigations we conduct. You'll see that within Unsubstantiated=
 there are now two categories, Unsubstantiated - Conclusive and Unsubstanti=
ated - Inconclusive. This extra category was added to give more context to =
the results of our team's investigative work. You mentioned, and I agree,  =
it might be helpful to share this with your investigators ahead of time so =
they can be aware and categorize their conclusions accurately before their =
final reports are send to you.

Let me know if you have any questions or concerns.

Conclusions
Definition
 Substantiated
The investigation found that the allegation more likely than not occurred, =
based on the available evidence.
Unsubstantiated - Conclusive
The investigation found sufficient evidence to conclude that the alleged co=
nduct, more likely than not, did not occur.
Unsubstantiated - Inconclusive
The investigation could not determine whether the alleged conduct occurred =
due to insufficient or conflicting evidence


Thanks,



